2 hour midterm, in-person through D2L
- Bring laptop
- Can write on paper, but might take longer, due to scanning document, etc
- No need for a calculator, can bring a simple calculator
- No phone? but given 5 mins for scanning at the end or can give to TA to scan and upload
- 2 TA invigilating
- Attendance of some sort
- Supposedly most should finish in 1 hr, dont need the whole 2 hr

Test is based on the PDF/slides, nothing is outside the scope of them
- Short answers, 5 questions
  - Answers should be less than half page or something
  - Like pro/cons of prototype model
  - Compare these two models: A and B. Define A and B
  - Give the different types of non-functional requirement
- Multiple choice questions, 10 questions
  - Some might have more than 1 answer: checkboxes, fill in the blanks?
  - Others will just have just one answer
- Might have to draw some diagram
  - They are simple, not complex. Can use online tools to draw (e.g. Draw.io, Visual Paradigm)
  - Like in Lecture 1, pg 20
  - Like in Lecture 2, pg 6 "Users of the requirements" know systems customers, managers, etc. don't need to know the description in detail
  - Waterfall model, prototype model, etc
  - Cost-value diagram
  - Don't have to be perfect
- Don't need to know the "Economic feasability" equations? like PV, NPV, ROI
  - But he apparently might give a question like Lecture 3, pg 34 "NPV: Example 1"
  - Whatever this is "(1+x)^n ≒ 1 + nx"
  - if there is a need for a formula, he might a formula sheet doc apparently, but you won't need it?
